title: Church of St Nicholas, Tingrith
text:
The Church of St Nicholas is a <a href="Listed%20building">Grade I listed</a> church in <a href="Tingrith">Tingrith</a>, <a href="Bedfordshire">Bedfordshire</a>, England. It became a listed building on 23 January 1961.
The brown sandstone walls date from the 15th century; the tracery of the windows is of white freestone.
